title: The Hustler
overview: An up-and-coming pool player plays a long-time champion in a single high-stakes match.

title: The Wrestler
overview: A faded professional wrestler must retire, but finds his quest for a new life outside the ring a dispiriting struggle.

title: Kai po che!
overview: Three friends growing up in India at the turn of the millennium set out to open a training academy to produce the country's next cricket stars.

title: Million Dollar Baby
overview: A determined woman works with a hardened boxing trainer to become a professional.

title: Chak De! India
overview: Kabir Khan is the coach of the Indian Women's National Hockey Team and his dream is to make his all girls team emerge victorious against all odds.

title: Il conformista
overview: A weak-willed Italian man becomes a fascist flunky who goes abroad to arrange the assassination of his old teacher, now a political dissident.

title: Black
overview: The cathartic tale of a young woman who can't see, hear or talk and the teacher who brings a ray of light into her dark world.

title: Creed
overview: The former World Heavyweight Champion Rocky Balboa serves as a trainer and mentor to Adonis Johnson, the son of his late friend and former rival Apollo Creed.

title: The Verdict
overview: A lawyer sees the chance to salvage his career and self-respect by taking a medical malpractice case to trial rather than settling.

title: Bacheha-Ye aseman
overview: After a boy loses his sister's pair of shoes, he goes on a series of adventures in order to find them. When he can't, he tries a new way to "win" a new pair.
stars: ['Mohammad Amir Naji', 'Amir Farrokh Hashemian', 'Bahare Seddiqi', 'Nafise Jafar-Mohammadi']

title: Ordinary People
overview: The accidental death of the older son of an affluent family deeply strains the relationships among the bitter mother, the good-natured father, and the guilt-ridden younger son.

title: Gattaca
overview: A genetically inferior man assumes the identity of a superior one in order to pursue his lifelong dream of space travel.

title: American History X
overview: A former neo-nazi skinhead tries to prevent his younger brother from going down the same wrong path that he did.

title: Capharnaüm
overview: While serving a five-year sentence for a violent crime, a 12-year-old boy sues his parents for neglect.
stars: ['Zain Al Rafeea', 'Yordanos Shiferaw', 'Boluwatife Treasure Bankole', 'Kawsar Al Haddad']

title: Jagten
overview: A teacher lives a lonely life, all the while struggling over his son's custody. His life slowly gets better as he finds love and receives good news from his son, but his new luck is about to be brutally shattered by an innocent little lie.

title: El ángel exterminador
overview: The guests at an upper-class dinner party find themselves unable to leave.

title: Detachment
overview: A substitute teacher who drifts from classroom to classroom finds a connection to the students and teachers during his latest assignment.

title: Nelyubov
overview: A couple going through a divorce must team up to find their son who has disappeared during one of their bitter arguments.

title: Fight Club
overview: An insomniac office worker and a devil-may-care soapmaker form an underground fight club that evolves into something much, much more.

title: The Help
overview: An aspiring author during the civil rights movement of the 1960s decides to write a book detailing the African American maids' point of view on the white families for which they work, and the hardships they go through on a daily basis.
